
[1]religiously

   RELIG'IOUSLY, adv.

   1. Piously; with love and reverence to the Supreme Being; in obedience
   to the divine commands.

   2. According to the rites of religion.

   3. Reverently; with veneration.

   4. Exactly; strictly; conscientiously; as a vow or promise religiously
   observed.
